CVS CHECKOUT:
- $ export CVS_RSH=ssh
  $ cvs -z3 -d:ext:coppit@cvs.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/cgicache co devel

This file is not distributed with CGI::Cache. It outlines some notes for
developers readying a set of files for distribution.

To test your distribution:
$ make clean
$ perl Makefile.PL
$ make
$ make test

After the functional tests have passed, make the distribution file:
$ make dist

Checklist for a release:
- Be sure to add new test cases for new features
- Diff with the script in the devel directory to make sure everything's
  kosher:
  $ ./nocvsdiff -r ../devel ../dist | less
- Make sure version number increases.
- Datestamp the changelog
- Edit version number in README.
- Add version changes to README and CHANGES.
- Update MANIFEST if necessary
- Make distribution file. (See above.)
- Install the distribution file elsewhere to test it.
  - scp CGI-Cache-X.XX.tar.gz coppit@linux.compile.sourceforge.net:.
  - ssh -l coppit linux.sourceforge.net
  or lately:
  - scp CGI-Cache-X.XX.tar.gz coppit@linux.sourceforge.net:.
  - ssh -l coppit linux.sourceforge.net

  - scp CGI-Cache-X.XX.tar.gz coppit@bsd.compile.sourceforge.net:.
  - ssh -l coppit bsd.compile.sourceforge.net
  or lately:
  - scp CGI-Cache-X.XX.tar.gz coppit@bsd.sourceforge.net:.
  - ssh -l coppit bsd.sourceforge.net
- Check in code:
  $ cvs ci
    (use your userid instead of coppit)
- Upload to CPAN:
  http://pause.perl.org/pause/authenquery
- Upload changelog:
  scp Changes coppit@cgicache.sourceforge.net:/home/groups/c/cg/cgicache/htdocs
- Upload to SourceForge:
  ncftpput upload.sourceforge.net /incoming CGI-Cache-X.XX.tar.gz
- Release file on SourceForge:
  http://sourceforge.net/account/login.php
  https://sourceforge.net/project/admin/qrs.php?package_id=&group_id=14586
- Announce news on SourceForge:
  http://sourceforge.net/news/submit.php?group_id=14586
- Update webpage:
  scp coppit@cgicache.sourceforge.net:/home/groups/c/cg/cgicache/htdocs/index.html .
  [edit URL & version]
  scp index.html coppit@cgicache.sourceforge.net:/home/groups/c/cg/cgicache/htdocs/
  rm index.htm
- Announce on freshmeat:
  http://freshmeat.net/add-release/1180/
- Announce it to cgicache-announce@sourceforge.net and to
  comp.lang.perl.announce.

